Class GenericNode<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.unibo.alchemist.model.implementations.nodes.GenericNode<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Concentration type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    INode<T>, Serializable, Comparable<INode<T>>, Iterable<IReaction<T>>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DoubleNode, IntegerNode, LsaNode, ProtelisNode

    public abstract class GenericNode<T>
extends Object
implements INode<T>
    This class realizes an abstract node. You may extend it to realize your own nodes.

    • Constructor Detail

      • GenericNode

        protected GenericNode(boolean threadLocal)
        Basically, builds the node and just caches the hash code.
        Parameters:
        threadLocal - true if the id should be local to the current thread. In order to keep the node ids along multiple simulations, pass true and use different threads to instance the nodes.
